08:48.795 --> 08:50.797
If it rained, he prayed.

08:50.863 --> 08:52.932
If he was late, he prayed.

08:53.000 --> 08:55.102
If he couldn't find his keys, he...

08:55.168 --> 08:56.769
He prayed, right.

08:56.836 --> 08:59.839
And you don't share his
interest in the Christian occult?

08:59.906 --> 09:02.075
Comrades...

09:02.142 --> 09:04.511
I'm just a baker.

09:04.577 --> 09:08.248
And Marku, he was a troubled boy.

09:08.315 --> 09:11.985
He spoke constantly of his faith.

09:12.052 --> 09:14.587
And why exactly didn't
you inform on him?

09:21.028 --> 09:24.031
How about a slice of bread?

09:28.335 --> 09:29.369
Hmm.

09:32.239 --> 09:36.176
Marku spoke often about
transubstantiation.

09:36.243 --> 09:38.345
Are you gents familiar with the term?

09:38.411 --> 09:41.114
Yeah. Transubstantiation.

09:41.181 --> 09:43.416
In countries that are slaves
to the Christian faith,

09:43.483 --> 09:45.718
they eat bread during
ritualized worship.

09:45.785 --> 09:47.054
They believe that the bread

09:47.120 --> 09:49.389
literally turns into the body of Christ.

09:49.456 --> 09:50.557
Correct.

09:50.623 --> 09:52.359
Think about that.

09:52.425 --> 09:54.861
One second, you're chewing on my bread,

09:54.927 --> 09:57.430
and the next moment, that
very same bread is transformed

09:57.497 --> 10:00.100
into the flesh of Jesus Christ.

10:00.167 --> 10:03.002
An absurd superstition.

10:03.070 --> 10:04.804
Let's hope so,

10:04.871 --> 10:10.810
or the two of you would've
just eaten the flesh of a man.

10:10.877 --> 10:13.012
(LAUGHING)

10:22.655 --> 10:24.591
