24:57.096 --> 24:59.498
♪ Are you ready for the sex girls? ♪

24:59.565 --> 25:02.401
♪ The fine, fine, super
special, real sex girls ♪

25:02.468 --> 25:06.305
♪ Are you ready for the best girls? ♪

25:06.372 --> 25:08.507
♪ The knees-showin', knees-
showin' big-breast girls. ♪

25:08.574 --> 25:10.576
(KNOCKS ON WINDOW, MUSIC TURNS OFF)

25:15.247 --> 25:19.785
I... I... I was just listening
for a second, that's all.

25:19.851 --> 25:22.121
I... I didn't mean... I...

25:38.270 --> 25:40.706
Listen, it's okay,
Flavia, I'm not angry.

25:40.772 --> 25:42.741
You're not?

25:42.808 --> 25:44.943
No.

25:46.045 --> 25:48.647
(SNIFFS)

25:48.714 --> 25:51.083
You're almost a grown woman,

25:51.150 --> 25:53.986
and so I'm gonna speak
to you like an adult.

25:59.491 --> 26:02.328
Flavia, do you know what a whore is?

26:02.394 --> 26:06.798
It's... it's a woman who
sleeps with men for money.

26:06.865 --> 26:08.000
Exactly.

26:08.067 --> 26:09.601
And do you think

26:09.668 --> 26:12.304
that there are little girls
out there that dream of one day

26:12.371 --> 26:14.240
growing up to become whores?

26:14.306 --> 26:16.475
No, Papa, of course not.

26:17.743 --> 26:19.245
No, of course not.

26:19.311 --> 26:23.082
And yet the world is full of them.

26:23.149 --> 26:26.152
The West wants to turn
us all into whores.

26:26.218 --> 26:30.789
And they're devious in their ways.

26:30.856 --> 26:33.692
But this is just music, Papa.

26:33.759 --> 26:36.762
No, Flavia, it's propaganda.

26:36.828 --> 26:41.100
It's propaganda designed
to break down your defenses,

26:41.167 --> 26:43.135
little by little, and they
call it "art" or "music"

26:43.202 --> 26:45.971
or "film" or "literature,"
but make no mistake

26:46.038 --> 26:48.140
what it really is.

26:48.207 --> 26:50.008
What is it really?

26:50.076 --> 26:52.744
A tool for brainwashing.

26:52.811 --> 26:56.115
Every time you listen
to one of these songs,

26:56.182 --> 27:00.052
you are being indoctrinated.

27:11.497 --> 27:15.434
Well, you didn't have to
break the radio, Flavia.

27:15.501 --> 27:17.703
You know, there's a Bartók
concerto on tomorrow.

27:22.208 --> 27:25.611
I've seen terrible things, Flavia.

27:25.677 --> 27:28.680
It's why I'm so protective of you.

27:28.747 --> 27:31.650
I love you, Papa.

27:34.120 --> 27:36.322
I love you, too.

27:39.158 --> 27:42.394
Mmm.

27:42.461 --> 27:45.664
That's one more thing that
I'll miss about this country.

27:45.731 --> 27:50.769
Romanians make love like no one else.

27:50.836 --> 27:53.339
Listen, Jane...

27:53.405 --> 27:54.640
(SIGHS)

27:54.706 --> 27:59.511
Father Streza happens to
have information that I need.

27:59.578 --> 28:01.947
Can you get him to talk to me?

28:02.013 --> 28:05.284
Gregor, don't ruin the moment.

28:05.351 --> 28:08.187
This man might have killed my partner.

28:08.254 --> 28:10.989
I understand if you have
religious convictions,

28:11.056 --> 28:12.391
but I need your help.

28:15.227 --> 28:16.562
Okay.

28:20.732 --> 28:23.502
Look, I'll be honest.

28:23.569 --> 28:27.706
Some of us in the West don't
actually believe in religion.

28:27.773 --> 28:31.042
We just pretend to in order to
convince a bunch of half-wits

28:31.109 --> 28:33.245
